<StringTableFile xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"><Name>02_cv_dunstan</Name><NextEntryID>53</NextEntryID><EntryCount>52</EntryCount><Entries><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>The dwarf bustles between a sweltering forge fire and a work table. He wipes one muscle-knotted arm across his brow. "If this is about the breastplates, I already told Clyver they won't be repaired till next week."</DefaultText><FemaleText>The dwarf bustles between a sweltering forge fire and a work table. He wipes one muscle-knotted arm across his brow. "If this is about the breastplates, I already told Clyver they won't be repaired till next week."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Something else on your mind?"</DefaultText><FemaleText>"Something else on your mind?"</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"I suppose Clyver's sent you down here to get me working on those forge knights, eh?"</DefaultText><FemaleText>"I suppose Clyver's sent you down here to get me working on those forge knights, eh?"</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>He turns from the forge, setting his hammer on the work table. "Eh? You need something?" Dunstan yells, as if deafened by repeated hammer blows.</DefaultText><FemaleText>He turns from the forge, setting his hammer on the work table. "Eh? You need something?" Dunstan yells, as if deafened by repeated hammer blows.</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Keep after 'em!"</DefaultText><FemaleText>"Keep after 'em!"</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>Dunstan's beard is matted. A trickle of blood runs along his jawline. Despite the dents in his armor, he looks strangely invigorated. 

