He runs a calloused finger along the edge of one of the shards. "This blade'll take some time, but I guarantee it'll be worth the wait."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Have you finished with the sword?"</DefaultText><FemaleText>"Have you finished with the sword?"</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Tell me about the Knights."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"Tell me about the Knights."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"We were all smiths back in Hadret's day, though I'm about the only one here who still gets his hands dirty." He laughs. "We're a fearsome fighting force, though these days I think Clyver takes more pride in our parade formations."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"We were all smiths back in Hadret's day, though I'm about the only one here who still gets his hands dirty." He laughs. "We're a fearsome fighting force, though these days I think Clyver takes more pride in our parade formations."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"I'm a forge master. I'm a master smith for the Crucible Knights, but the way I see it, I'm also keeping up with our old traditions. The first members of our order were smiths - nowadays, most everyone's a professional soldier."

